eath_place        = \n| residence          = [[Los Angeles]], [[California]], U.S.\n| nationality        = [[Americans|American]]\n| other_names        = \n| education          = [[University of Southern California]] (B.A., 2009)<ref name=\"bee audio\"/>\n| occupation         = Voice actor\n| years_active       = <!-- NEED SOURCE 2006-present -->\n| spouse = {{marriage|Julia McIlvaine|2020|}}\n| home_town          = [[Las Vegas]], [[Nevada]], U.S.<ref name=\"afterbuzz interview\">{{cite web|url=http://www.afterbuzztv.com/2016/11/27/ray-chase-interview-afterbuzz-tvs-the-voice-of/|title=Ray Chase Interview - AfterBuzz TV's The Voice Of|author=|date=November 27, 2016|website=afterbuzztv.com|accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n| website            = {{URL|http://www.raychase.com/}}\n}}\n'''Ray Chase''' (born May 20, 1987) is an American voice actor who has voiced in anime, animations, video games and audiobooks.<ref name=\"bee audio\">{{cite web|title=BeeAudio: Ray Chase|url=https://www.beeaudio.com/narrator/ray-chase}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Exclusive Interview with Ray Chase at Anime Weekend Atlanta 2016|url=http://talknerdywithus.com/2016/10/02/exclusive-interview-with-ray-chase-at-anime-weekend-atlanta-2016/|last=Fulks|first=Carey|work=Talk Nerdy With Us|date=October 2, 2016|accessdate=March 23, 2017}}</ref> His best known role is [[Noctis Lucis Caelum]], the main character in ''[[Final Fantasy XV]].''<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.craveonline.com/entertainment/1172677-interview-final-fantasy-xvs-ray-chase-talks-noctis-female-characters-voice-actors-strike|title=Interview {{!}} Final Fantasy XV's Ray Chase Talks Noctis, Female Characters and the Voice Actors' Strike - CraveOnline|date=November 30, 2016|work=CraveOnline|access-date=April 22, 2017|language=en-US}}</ref> He is also known for his voice performances as Eve in ''[[Nier: Automata]]'', Artorius Colbrande from ''[[Tales of Berseria]]'', Roy from '' [[Fire Emblem]]'', Yu Otosaka from [[Charlotte (anime)|''Charlotte'']], and Bruno Bucciarati In ''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure: Golden Wind]]''.\n\n==Filmography==\n===Anime===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ List of dubbing performances in anime\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! Notes\n! Source\n|-\n| {{dts|2015|11|01|format=y}} || ''[[The Seven Deadly Sins (manga)|The Seven Deadly Sins]]'' || Howzer || || Tweet<ref>{{cite tweet | first=Ray | last=Chase | user=raychase | number=660888217810399232 | date=November 1, 2015 | title=So excited! My first big part in an anime, and its on Netflix now! Listen to all episodes with me as Howzer today! | accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015 ||''[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure (2012 TV series)|JoJo's Bizarre Adventure]]''|| Donovan / Loggins ||[[JoJo's Bizarre Adventure (season 1)|Battle Tendancy]]\n| Tweet<ref>{{cite tweet | date=July 3, 2017 | user=RayChase | number=882129177310183424  |title=I was actually in the first two seasons as well, Donavan and Loggins!  | accessdate=November 28, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{dts|2016|04|16|format=y}}\u201317 || ''[[Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011 TV series)|Hunter \u00d7 Hunter]]'' || Hanzo, Squala, Geretta || 2011 series || <ref>''[[Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011 TV series)|Hunter \u00d7 Hunter]]'' credits:\n* {{cite episode | time=Closing credits | title= Departure \u00d7 And \u00d7 Friends | publisher=Viz Media | episodelink=List of Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011) episodes#ep1 | series=Hunter \u00d7 Hunter | network=Adult Swim | airdate=April 16, 2016 | number=1}}\n* {{cite episode | time=Closing credits | title= Rivals \u00d7 for \u00d7 Survival | publisher=Viz Media | episodelink=List of Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011) episodes#ep3 | series=Hunter \u00d7 Hunter | network=Adult Swim | airdate=April 30, 2016 | number=3}}\n* {{cite episode | time=Closing credits | title= Hope \u00d7 and \u00d7 Ambition | publisher=Viz Media | episodelink=List of Hunter \u00d7 Hunter (2011) episodes#ep4 | series=Hunter \u00d7 Hunter | network=Adult Swim | 