tly killed along with the rest of Legion when they were converted into energy to fuel the Omni-Wave<ref name=\"Avengers vol. 3 #7\"/>\n* '''Captain Glory (Gla-Ree)'''<ref>''Avengers'' #676. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A Kree who is a member of the alien version of the [[Lethal Legion]].\n* '''[[Hala the Accuser]]'''<ref>''Guardians of Knowhere'' #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A member of the Kree's Accuser Corps.\n* '''Hav-Ak'''<ref name=\"Captain Marvel vol. 4 #1\">''Captain Marvel'' vol. 4 #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A member of the Kree Peace Battalion; later killed<ref name=\"captain-marvel4\"/>\n* '''House of Fiyero'''<ref name=\"Annihilation: Ronan #1\">''Annihilation: Ronan'' #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 The ruling house on Hala who ordered that the Supreme Intelligence be lobotomized. They later saw Ronan as a threat and gave Tana Nile information on Thanos in exchange for framing Ronan for conspiring against them. The House of Fiyero attempted an alliance with Annihilation Wave, but were all killed by Ronan.<ref name=\"Annihilation #5\">''Annihilation'' #5</ref>\n* '''Huran the Accuser'''<ref>''FF'' #6. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A previous member of the Kree's Accuser Corps thousands of years ago. \n* '''Jat Vor-Thrul'''<ref>''X-Men: Legacy'' #220. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 Kree Cyborg who was a pirate. He was the engineer of the crew known as the Salvagers. \n* '''Jella'''<ref name=\"Captain Marvel vol. 4 #1\"/>&nbsp;\u2013 member of the Kree Peace Battalion; later killed<ref name=\"captain-marvel4\"/>\n* '''Jul'''<ref name=\"Nova5\"/>&nbsp;\u2013 A Kree who was killed by the Phalanx<ref name=\"Nova5\"/>\n* '''Kaer-Linn'''<ref name=\"Silver Surfer vol. 3 #53\"/>&nbsp;\u2013 A forgotten Kree scientist. Dr. Kaer-Linn built the Silver Surfer robot that executed Clumsy Foulup and General Dwi-Zann. He in turn was killed by General Ael-Dan.\n* '''Kalum Fahr'''<ref name=\"inhumans1\">''Inhumans'' vol. 2 #1. Marvel Comics.