killed by a Kree Kleaner for betraying the Empire.<ref>''Life of Captain Marvel'' Vol 2 #5</ref>\n* '''Maston-Dar'''<ref>''Inhumans: The Great Refuge''. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A Kree general that once led the Kree forces to reclaim the Blue Area of the Moon from the Inhumans.\n* '''[[Doctor Minerva|Doctor Minerva (Minn-Erva)]]'''<ref>''[[Captain Marvel (Marvel Comics)|Captain Marvel]] #50'' (April 1977). Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A member of Starforce; a geneticist who attempted to mate with Mar-Vell to sire a superior offspring to advance the evolutionary potential of the Kree; used the Psyche-Magnitron to duplicate the powers of Ms. Marvel.\n* '''[[Imperial Guard (comics)|M-Nell (Commando)]]'''<ref name=\"Imperial Guard #1\">''Imperial Guard'' #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 member of the Imperial Guard; joined to symbolize unity between Kree and Shi'ar\n* '''Mon-Tog'''<ref>''Inhumans'' #10. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A black Kree who is the commander of an outpost near Stent\n* '''Morag'''<ref>''[[Avengers (comics)|Avengers]] #133'' (March 1975). Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 a Kree tribal leader from ions ago who oversaw the construction of the Blue Area of the Moon\n* '''Murius'''<ref name=\"Inhumans #4\">''Inhumans'' #4. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 wife of Falzon and mother of Shatterstar (Arides); later killed by her son<ref name=\"Inhumans #4\"/>\n* '''Nenora'''<ref>''Silver Surfer Annual'' vol. 3 #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 Also known as Agent K6; Skrull that infiltrated Kree; former lover of Aptak and agent of Kylor; former chief coordinator of the Supreme Intelligence; she secretly informed Skrulls of Kree plans, until she became the Kree Empire's leader; she was revealed to be a Skrull by S'byll and deposed.<ref name=\"Silver Surfer vol. 3 #30\">''Silver Surfer'' vol. 3 #30</ref>\n* '''[[Noh-Varr]]'''<ref>''Marvel Boy'' vol. 2 #1. Marvel Comics.</ref>&nbsp;\u2013 A Kree soldier from a parallel reality, called 