{"title_page": "SHESHA (musician)", "text_new": "{{short description|Malaysian rapper, singer, songwriter, record producer}}\n{{redirect|SHESHA||Shesha (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = SHESHA\n| image            = \n| caption          = 2020\n| birth_name       = Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi\n| alias            = {{hlist|SHESHA|Sha Zovve|Fadeproof}}\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1987|11|18}}\n| birth_place      = [[Bukit Mertajam, Penang]], Malaysia\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n* Rapper\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Record Producer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2005\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist <!-- See WP:WikiProject Musicians -->|embed=yes\n| background   = solo_singer<!--includes rappers-->\n| instrument   = Vocals, Synthesizer\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[pop-rap]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Electronic music]]\n}}\n| label        = {{flatlist|\n* Bimasakti Records \n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* Pistah Few\n}}\n| website = {{URL|sheshaofficial.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi''' (born November 18, 1987), known professionally as '''SHESHA''' (stylized as '''SHESH\u0245'''), is a Malaysian rapper, singer, songwriter and record producer. \n\n==Early life==\nSHESHA was born as Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi on 18 November 1987 in [[Bukit Mertajam]], [[Penang]], [[Malaysia]]. His mother Indera was a housewife, and his father Andrew Sivam was a store supervisor. His ancestors hailed from [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]] and also [[Coimbatore]], [[Madurai]], [[Tamil Nadu]]. He is the eldest of two siblings in a family consisting a sister (Patricia Sivagamy).\n\nSHESHA had his primary education at the '''Sekolah Kebangsaan Tunku Abdul Malik''' in [[Kulim]], [[Kedah]], [[Malaysia]]. As a child he had a great interest in badminton and chess. After his primary, SHESHA was enrolled at the '''Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Kulim''' . Upon completion of his school education, SHESHA performed several jobs like telemarketer, waiting staff, bartender and disc jockey while pursuing his studies in engineering in Penang. Quitting his studies in Penang, SHESHA left to Kuala Lumpur to pursue his music career. Performing several jobs like manual labour and customer service representative. Later on decided to take up sound & music course in [[Limkokwing University of Creative Technology]]. His relative and friends motivated him to join the university and supported him during this phase. SHESHA graduated with a full scholarship aid given by Tan Sri Dato\u2019 Sri Paduka Dr Limkokwing.\n\n==Career==\n===2005\u20132008===\nSHESHA under the moniker Fadeproof together with his comrades, Avathara and MC Hesh formed a band called '''Pistah Few''', influenced by the Malaysian Hip hop Group, [[Poetic Ammo]]. For two years, they ventured out as a band and serenaded local events like prom nights and cultural shows. This provided them with the opportunity to further sharpen their showmanship, emceeing skills and songwriting. Their first break rose when [[Gang Starz]], a reality television show of [[TV3 (Malaysia)|TV3]] Malaysia held its audition at Sheraton Hotel, Penang in 2007. Pistah Few was judged by Cat Farish; actor, singer and record producer and also Juliza Adzlizan; actor, singer and vocal teacher. Pistah Few\u2019s performance of self-written and composed song '''Flamethrowah''' truly awed the judges, thus enabling them to represent the northern region for the national level audition in [[Istana Budaya]], [[Kuala Lumpur]].\n\nThough they failed to proceed further, competing among groups from South East Asia provided the trio with the much needed exposure and experience to further hone musical skills and learn what\u2019s required to succeed professionally.Meeting DJ Chaoz at Gang Starz audition further led them to be introduced to the Penang Urban music scene and to perform gigs around Penang. They had the golden chances of performing at Urban Volume 2 by DJ Laze, Urban Showdown by Muneer of Urban Method along artistes like Altimet, Northsyde, Royal Maximus and many more.Soon, Pistah Few became a duo. Avathara and SHESHA continued. In 2008, Pistah Few won the competition held by ECHO PARK Penang. Hip Hop RnB Extravaganza was judged by Simon Michael (One in A Million - season 3 - finalist). In the same year, they performed for a notable charity event called 30 Hour Famine 2008 by [[World Vision International|World Vision]] Malaysia in KL. In 2008 too, SHESHA performed with Dareyno of Junio Hustle at Ambang Merdeka 2008 at [[Genting Highlands]], along with artistes like Ruffedge, Roshan Jamrock, [[Goldkartz]] and Henley.\n\n===2009\u20132013===\nIn the following year, he met T.A.Santhanam, a professional [[Thavil|Thavil]] player, with whom he worked on a project known as Vaanam, a tamil pop compilation album. Under the production and watchful eye of T.A.Santhanam, SHESHA worked with artists like [[M. L. R. Karthikeyan|MLR Karthikeyan]], Ganesan Manoharan ([[Astro (television)|Astro]] Vanavil Superstar Champion), Avathara (Pistah Few) and many more. Musicians from Chennai,Tamil Nadu, India were brought into the project; M.S.V Raja (Saxophone), Kamalkhar (Woodwind) and Eshwar Rao (Sitar). Music arrangers were Navin, a Malaysian Indian Music Industry (MIMI) Award winner and Mixing Engineer, Suresh Raaj (Chennai). SHESHA was featured for two songs in that album ; Unnai Parthe Pinbu and Vaa vaa Vasegaara. After 2 years, in 2012, Vaanam was released. . The following year ''Unnai Parthe Pinbu'' was nominated for [[Malaysian Music Awards|Anugerah Industri Muzik]] and [[VIMA Music Awards]].\n\n===2014\u20132019===\nSHESHA under the moniker Sha Zovve, produced the soundtrack ' ''Yaar Enbathey (Crazy Mix)'' ' for a tamil short film ' ''David'' ' which was in [[Raaga (radio station)|THR Raaga]] Malaysian Top 10 for 5 weeks. ''David'' was the first short film in Malaysia to distribute Callertunes for its soundtrack. He was also actively involved in film, television and music video production; ' ''Made For Each Other'' ' a [[Malayalam|Malayalam]] program made by ''Manorama TV'' [[Kerala|Kerala]], ' ''Yaali'' ' a film by [[Akshaya Rao|Akshaya Rao]], ' ''Kamalini'' ', ' ''Thedal'' ', ' ''Azhagey'' ' and more. SHESHA acted in [[Cinemax|Cinemax]] series [[Strike Back (TV series)|Strike Back]]: [[Strike Back: Revolution|Revolution]] as a insurgent, [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia|RTM]] series ' ''Dr.Love'' ' as a radio jockey. He also did lead roles in [[Public service announcement|PSA]] and short films; ' ''A Strangers Pleasure'' ', ' ''Sita'' ', ' ''The Cookbook'' '. SHESHA was nominated for [[BMW|BMW]] Shorties Best Sound Design category for ' ''The Cookbook'' '. In 2016, he produced ' ''En Jeeven Nee (ARR ANTHEM)'' ', a tribute for [[A. R. Rahman|A.R.Rahman]] Live In Concert which was held in [[Stadium Merdeka|Stadium Merdeka]], Malaysia. ' ''En Jeeven Nee'' ' was in [[Raaga (radio station)|THR Raaga]] Malaysian Top 10 for 8 weeks. Charting Number #2 in the first five weeks and Number #1 in the final three weeks. SHESHA produced signature tune for ''Malik Streams Corporation'', which was distributed  for the release of [[Theri (film)|Theri]] & [[Kabali (film)|Kabali]] in Malaysia. He was also the Audio Engineer for [[Kabali (film)|Kabali]] [[Malay language|Malay]] version trailer release. SHESHA produced the [[Soundtrack album|Soundtrack album]] for the film ' ''Villavan-The Vigilante'' ' which was released in 2018, featuring [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]], [[Shweta Mohan]], [[Suchith Suresan]], [[Keba Jeremiah]], [[Maria Roe Vincent]], Hyde Karty, Vassan Nassav, Avathara, Aneithazef, Meerlyn, El F\u00c9 Choir and many other artist . The soundtracks from the album was nominated for [[VIMA Music Awards]] in few categories. The following year, he produced the theme song ' ''Fabulous Lady'' ' for ''Mrs Fabulous Malaysia'' event, featuring Malaysian artist Maya Hanum.\n\n===2020\u2013present===\nIn 2020, he rebranded himself as '''SHESHA''' and started a new label, '''Bimasakti Records'''. The debut release '''Bintang EP''' is in final stage of its production, slated to release later this year.\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n;EP\n*2020: ''Bintang EP''\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n\n=== [[Malaysian Music Awards|Anugerah Industri Muzik]] ===\n\n*2013: Nominated for Best Hip Hop/Rap Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 Anugerah Industri Muzik (AIM) Malaysian-Indian.<ref>https://www.aim.org.my/pdf/AIMMalaysian-Indian/AIM%20Malaysian-Indian%202013-Final%205%20List.pdf</ref>\n\n=== [[VIMA Music Awards]] ===\n\n*2013: Nominated for Best Tamil/Punjabi Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 VIMA Music Awards.<ref>https://hype.my/2013/18884/vima-malaysia-final-nominees-list/</ref>\n*2013: Nominated for Best Genre-Bender Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 VIMA Music Awards.\n*2018: Nominated for Best Pop Song Awards for \u2018Podu Sakka Podu\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.<ref>https://globalvima.com/2018/11/10/vima-2018-releases-official-nominees-list/</ref>\n*2018: Nominated for Best Indian/Punjabi Song Awards for \u2018Podu Sakka Podu\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.\n*2018: Nominated for Best Genre-Bender Song Awards for \u2018You Know !\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.\n\n=== Competitions ===\n*2006: '''[[TV3 (Malaysia)|TV3]] [[Gang Starz]]''' - '''Season 1''' ''(Top 15 Finalist)''\n*2008: '''ECHO PARK Hip Hop RnB Extravaganza''' - '''Group Category''' ''(Champion)'' \n*2008: '''GLO RAP''' - '''Solo Category''' ''(Champion)''\n*2015: '''BMW Shorties Best Sound Design Award for ''The Cookbook''.''' ''(Nominee)''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:SHESHA}}\n[[:Category:1987 births]]\n[[:Category:Living people]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian hip hop singers]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian rappers]]\n[[:Category:Malay-language singers]]\n[[:Category:English-language singers from Malaysia]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian people of Indian descent]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian businesspeople]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Malaysian rapper, singer, songwriter, record producer}}\n{{redirect|SHESHA||Shesha (disambiguation)}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name             = SHESHA\n| image            = \n| caption          = 2020\n| birth_name       = Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi\n| alias            = {{hlist|SHESHA|Sha Zovve|Fadeproof}}\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|1987|11|18}}\n| birth_place      = [[Bukit Mertajam, Penang]], Malaysia\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n* Rapper\n* Singer\n* Songwriter\n* Record Producer\n}}\n| years_active       = 2005\u2013present\n| module             = {{Infobox musical artist <!-- See WP:WikiProject Musicians -->|embed=yes\n| background   = solo_singer<!--includes rappers-->\n| instrument   = Vocals, Synthesizer\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Hip hop music|Hip hop]]\n* [[pop-rap]]\n* [[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]\n* [[Electronic music]]\n}}\n| label        = {{flatlist|\n* Bimasakti Records \n}}\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist|\n* Pistah Few\n}}\n| website = {{URL|sheshaofficial.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi''' (born November 18, 1987), known professionally as '''SHESHA''' (stylized as '''SHESH\u0245'''), is a Malaysian rapper, singer, songwriter and record producer. \n\n==Early life==\nSHESHA was born as Patrick Namasivayam Seshasahi on 18 November 1987 in [[Bukit Mertajam]], [[Penang]], [[Malaysia]]. His mother Indera was a housewife, and his father Andrew Sivam was a store supervisor. His ancestors hailed from [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]] and also [[Coimbatore]], [[Madurai]], [[Tamil Nadu]]. He is the eldest of two siblings in a family consisting a sister (Patricia Sivagamy).\n\nSHESHA had his primary education at the '''Sekolah Kebangsaan Tunku Abdul Malik''' in [[Kulim]], [[Kedah]], [[Malaysia]]. As a child he had a great interest in badminton and chess. After his primary, SHESHA was enrolled at the '''Sekolah Menengah Kebangsaan Kulim''' . Upon completion of his school education, SHESHA performed several jobs like telemarketer, waiting staff, bartender and disc jockey while pursuing his studies in engineering in Penang. Quitting his studies in Penang, SHESHA left to Kuala Lumpur to pursue his music career. Performing several jobs like manual labour and customer service representative. Later on decided to take up sound & music course in [[Limkokwing University of Creative Technology]]. His relative and friends motivated him to join the university and supported him during this phase. SHESHA graduated with a full scholarship aid given by Tan Sri Dato\u2019 Sri Paduka Dr Limkokwing.\n\n==Career==\n===2005\u20132008===\nSHESHA under the moniker Fadeproof together with his comrades, Avathara and MC Hesh formed a band called '''Pistah Few''', influenced by the Malaysian Hip hop Group, [[Poetic Ammo]]. For two years, they ventured out as a band and serenaded local events like prom nights and cultural shows. This provided them with the opportunity to further sharpen their showmanship, emceeing skills and songwriting. Their first break rose when [[Gang Starz]], a reality television show of [[TV3 (Malaysia)|TV3]] Malaysia held its audition at Sheraton Hotel, Penang in 2007. Pistah Few was judged by Cat Farish, a popular actor, singer and record producer and also Juliza Adzlizan, a popular actor, singer and vocal teacher. Pistah Few\u2019s performance of self-written and composed song '''Flamethrowah''' truly awed the judges, thus enabling them to represent the northern region for the national level audition in [[Istana Budaya]], [[Kuala Lumpur]].\n\nThough they failed to proceed further, competing among groups from South East Asia provided the trio with the much needed exposure and experience to further hone musical skills and learn what\u2019s required to succeed professionally.Meeting DJ Chaoz at Gang Starz audition further led them to be introduced to the Penang Urban music scene and to perform gigs around Penang. They had the golden chances of performing at Urban Volume 2 by DJ Laze, Urban Showdown by Muneer of Urban Method along artistes like Altimet, Northsyde, Royal Maximus and many more.Soon, Pistah Few became a duo. Avathara and SHESHA continued. In 2008, Pistah Few won the competition held by ECHO PARK Penang. Hip Hop RnB Extravaganza was judged by Simon Michael (One in A Million - season 3 - finalist). In the same year, they performed for a notable charity event called 30 Hour Famine 2008 by [[World Vision International|World Vision]] Malaysia in KL. In 2008 too, SHESHA performed with Dareyno of Junio Hustle at Ambang Merdeka 2008 at [[Genting Highlands]], along with artistes like Ruffedge, Roshan Jamrock, [[Goldkartz]] and Henley.\n\n===2009\u20132013===\nIn the following year, he met T.A.Santhanam, a professional [[Thavil|Thavil]] player, with whom he worked on a project known as Vaanam, a tamil pop compilation album. Under the production and watchful eye of T.A.Santhanam, SHESHA worked with artists like [[M. L. R. Karthikeyan|MLR Karthikeyan]], Ganesan Manoharan ([[Astro (television)|Astro]] Vanavil Superstar Champion), Avathara (Pistah Few) and many more. Musicians from Chennai,Tamil Nadu, India were brought into the project; M.S.V Raja (Saxophone), Kamalkhar (Woodwind) and Eshwar Rao (Sitar). Music arrangers were Navin, a Malaysian Indian Music Industry (MIMI) Award winner and Mixing Engineer, Suresh Raaj (Chennai). SHESHA was featured for two songs in that album ; Unnai Parthe Pinbu and Vaa vaa Vasegaara. After 2 years, in 2012, Vaanam was released. . The following year ''Unnai Parthe Pinbu'' was nominated for [[Malaysian Music Awards|Anugerah Industri Muzik]] and [[VIMA Music Awards]].\n\n===2014\u20132019===\nSHESHA under the moniker Sha Zovve, produced the soundtrack ' ''Yaar Enbathey (Crazy Mix)'' ' for a tamil short film ' ''David'' ' which was in [[Raaga (radio station)|THR Raaga]] Malaysian Top 10 for 5 weeks. ''David'' was the first short film in Malaysia to distribute Callertunes for its soundtrack. He was also actively involved in film, television and music video production; ' ''Made For Each Other'' ' a [[Malayalam|Malayalam]] program made by ''Manorama TV'' [[Kerala|Kerala]], ' ''Yaali'' ' a film by [[Akshaya Rao|Akshaya Rao]], ' ''Kamalini'' ', ' ''Thedal'' ', ' ''Azhagey'' ' and more. SHESHA acted in [[Cinemax|Cinemax]] series [[Strike Back (TV series)|Strike Back]]: [[Strike Back: Revolution|Revolution]] as a insurgent, [[Radio Televisyen Malaysia|RTM]] series ' ''Dr.Love'' ' as a radio jockey. He also did lead roles in [[Public service announcement|PSA]] and short films; ' ''A Strangers Pleasure'' ', ' ''Sita'' ', ' ''The Cookbook'' '. SHESHA was nominated for [[BMW|BMW]] Shorties Best Sound Design category for ' ''The Cookbook'' '. In 2016, he produced ' ''En Jeeven Nee (ARR ANTHEM)'' ', a tribute for [[A. R. Rahman|A.R.Rahman]] Live In Concert which was held in [[Stadium Merdeka|Stadium Merdeka]], Malaysia. ' ''En Jeeven Nee'' ' was in [[Raaga (radio station)|THR Raaga]] Malaysian Top 10 for 8 weeks. Charting Number #2 in the first five weeks and Number #1 in the final three weeks. SHESHA produced signature tune for ''Malik Streams Corporation'', which was distributed  for the release of [[Theri (film)|Theri]] & [[Kabali (film)|Kabali]] in Malaysia. He was also the Audio Engineer for [[Kabali (film)|Kabali]] [[Malay language|Malay]] version trailer release. SHESHA produced the [[Soundtrack album|Soundtrack album]] for the film ' ''Villavan-The Vigilante'' ' which was released in 2018, featuring [[Karthik (singer)|Karthik]], [[Shweta Mohan]], [[Suchith Suresan]], [[Keba Jeremiah]], [[Maria Roe Vincent]], Hyde Karty, Vassan Nassav, Avathara, Aneithazef, Meerlyn, El F\u00c9 Choir and many other artist . The soundtracks from the album was nominated for [[VIMA Music Awards]] in few categories. The following year, he produced the theme song ' ''Fabulous Lady'' ' for ''Mrs Fabulous Malaysia'' event, featuring Malaysian artist Maya Hanum.\n\n===2020\u2013present===\nIn 2020, he rebranded himself as '''SHESHA''' and started a new label, '''Bimasakti Records'''. The debut release '''Bintang EP''' is in final stage of its production, slated to release later this year.\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n;EP\n*2020: ''Bintang EP''\n\n==Awards and achievements==\n\n=== [[Malaysian Music Awards|Anugerah Industri Muzik]] ===\n\n*2013: Nominated for Best Hip Hop/Rap Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 Anugerah Industri Muzik (AIM) Malaysian-Indian.<ref>https://www.aim.org.my/pdf/AIMMalaysian-Indian/AIM%20Malaysian-Indian%202013-Final%205%20List.pdf</ref>\n\n=== [[VIMA Music Awards]] ===\n\n*2013: Nominated for Best Tamil/Punjabi Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 VIMA Music Awards.<ref>https://hype.my/2013/18884/vima-malaysia-final-nominees-list/</ref>\n*2013: Nominated for Best Genre-Bender Song Awards for \u2018Unnai Parthe Pinbu\u2019 at the 2013 VIMA Music Awards.\n*2018: Nominated for Best Pop Song Awards for \u2018Podu Sakka Podu\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.<ref>https://globalvima.com/2018/11/10/vima-2018-releases-official-nominees-list/</ref>\n*2018: Nominated for Best Indian/Punjabi Song Awards for \u2018Podu Sakka Podu\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.\n*2018: Nominated for Best Genre-Bender Song Awards for \u2018You Know !\u2019 at the 2018 VIMA Music Awards.\n\n=== Competitions ===\n*2006: '''[[TV3 (Malaysia)|TV3]] [[Gang Starz]]''' - '''Season 1''' ''(Top 15 Finalist)''\n*2008: '''ECHO PARK Hip Hop RnB Extravaganza''' - '''Group Category''' ''(Champion)'' \n*2008: '''GLO RAP''' - '''Solo Category''' ''(Champion)''\n*2015: '''BMW Shorties Best Sound Design Award for ''The Cookbook''.''' ''(Nominee)''\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:SHESHA}}\n[[:Category:1987 births]]\n[[:Category:Living people]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian male singer-songwriters]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian hip hop singers]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian rhythm and blues singers]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian rappers]]\n[[:Category:Malay-language singers]]\n[[:Category:English-language singers from Malaysia]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian people of Indian descent]]\n[[:Category:Malaysian businesspeople]]\n", "name_user": "Sarveshvara99", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200e2005\u20132008", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHESHA_(musician)"}
{"title_page": "Imperfect Circle", "text_new": "{{for|the ''Under the Dome'' episode|Imperfect Circles}}\n{{use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{use list-defined references|date=August 2019}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name = Imperfect Circle\n| type = studio\n| artist = [[Hootie & the Blowfish]]\n| cover = Hootie & the Blowfish - Imperfect Circle.jpg\n| alt = A blue-green background with the album title and artist name written on it\n| released = {{start date|2019|11|1}}\n| recorded = 2018\n| studio = \n| genre = {{hlist|[[Country music|Country]]<ref name=\"bbtl\" />|[[Rock music|rock]]<ref name=\"st\" />}}\n| length = 42:31\n| label = [[Capitol Records Nashville|Capitol Nashville]]\n| producer = {{hlist|[[Frank Rogers (record producer)|Frank Rogers]]|[[Jeff Trott]]}}\n| prev_title = [[Live in Charleston]]\n| prev_year = 2006\n| year = 2019\n| next_title = \n| next_year = \n| misc = {{Extra chronology\n| artist     = [[Hootie & the Blowfish]] studio album\n| type = studio\n| prev_title = [[Looking for Lucky]]\n| prev_year  = 2005\n| title      = Imperfect Circle\n| year       = 2019\n| next_title =\n| next_year  =\n}} \n{{Singles\n | name        = Imperfect Circle\n | type        = studio\n | single1     = Rollin'\n | single1date = September 6, 2019\n | single2     = Miss California\n | single2date = September 20, 2019\n | single3     = Lonely on a Saturday Night\n | single3date = October 4, 2019\n | single4     = Hold On\n | single4date = October 17, 2019\n | single5     = Turn It Up\n | single5date = October 25, 2019\n}}\n}}\n\n'''''Imperfect Circle''''' is the sixth studio album by American rock band [[Hootie & the Blowfish]], released on [[Capitol Records Nashville]] on November 1, 2019.<ref name=\"bb\" /> It is their first new studio album in fourteen years; it has received mixed reviews and modest commercial success.\n\n==Recording and release==\nThe album was announced in December 2018, along with their [[Group Therapy Tour]], the first outing the band had made since 2008.<ref name=\"ap\" /> Once the group decided to reform, they went to vocalist [[Darius Rucker]]'s management company to help them arrange for recording and promotion.<ref name=\"gn\" /> The band members decided to record again concurrent with the decision to tour<ref name=\"cst\" /> and used the opportunity to debut new tracks live.<ref name=\"js\" /> This release is the first from the band in 14&nbsp;years and the title was announced on August 9, 2019.<ref name=\"bb\" />\n\nTo promote the album, the single \"Rollin'\" was made available with pre-orders on their site and to the general public on September 6.<ref name=\"bb\" /> The band enlisted [[Frank Rogers (record producer)|Frank Rogers]] and [[Jeff Trott]] to record them, along with a variety of guest musicians.<ref name=\"usa\" /> Individual band members brought in songs that they had considered for solo efforts (guitarist [[Mark Bryan]], with \"Turn It Up\") or that resulted from [[jam session]]s (singer [[Darius Rucker]] with pop musician [[Ed Sheeran]] on \"Wildfire Love\"), finally arriving at 17 tracks recorded in the studio.<ref name=\"rs\" /> The band worked with outside songwriters for this recording, admonishing them, \"We don\u2019t want you to write the Hootie song... Write a song and we\u2019ll make it sound like Hootie.\"<ref name=\"america\" /> The goal for songwriting was authenticity and an ability to speak to the average person.<ref name=\"people\" />\n\nThe band released the track listing and lead single \"Rollin\u2019\" on September 5.<ref name=\"bbtl\" /> \"Miss California\" and \"Lonely on a Saturday Night\" followed, with \"Hold On\" coming out on October 18.<ref name=\"ho\" /> Some sources indicated that the song \"Unafraid\" would be on the final release but it was cut.<ref name=\"rs\" />\n\n==Reception==\nThe band's hometown paper, ''[[The Post and Courier]]'' ran a negative review written by [[Associated Press]] writer Mark Kennedy, who acknowledged some solid musicality but ultimately concluded that the album is made up of \"utterly forgettable songs\" and \"nothing on this album is fresh\".<ref name=\"pandc\" /> A second review in the same paper from their local writer Kalyn Oyer was more positive.<ref name=\"pandc2\" /> In [[Consequence of Sound]], Tyler Clark awarded the album a C\u2013, calling it \"painfully bland\" but praises Rucker's vocals and lyrics.<ref name=\"cos\" /> The editorial staff of [[AllMusic Guide]] gave the release four out of five stars, with reviewer [[Stephen Thomas Erlewine]] called this \"a nice blend between the group's signature college rock singalongs and Rucker's slick, cheerful solo work\" and praised the album's positive feel, writing, \"This friendliness lends itself to a collection of songs that are resolutely sturdy, designed to sound more charming over time, and the inherent warmth of Imperfect Circle is reason enough to give the tunes a chance to grow.\"<ref name=\"amg\" /> The ''[[Texarkana Gazette]]'' published a mixed interview that called the songs \"earnest and yet utterly forgettable\" which are \"nice when you play them but make no discernible impression\".<ref name=\"tg\" /> Ken Tucker of ''[[Fresh Air]]'' opines \"This collection manages the tricky challenge of sounding like classic Hootie while also extending the group's sound for the 21st century\", calling it \"a well-made, frequently thoughtful album\".<ref name=\"fa\" />\n\n==Just as 2.0x you toy==\nCan is nose and days Saturday 2020 october.\n\nP.s. C.D CDIVO up know if involved [[Portugese|Here.]]\n\nhaving &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n\n==Track listing==\n#\"New Year's Day\" (Tofer Brown, Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh, [[Eric Paslay]], Je\ufb00 Trott)&nbsp;\u2013 3:32\n#\"Miss California\" (Andrew DeRoberts, David Ryan Harris, Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh)&nbsp;\u2013 3:12\n#\"Wild Fire Love\" ([[Joel Crouse]], Kyle Rife, [[Darius Rucker]], [[Ed Sheeran]])&nbsp;\u2013 3:33\n#\"Hold On\" ([[Jim Beavers]], [[Chris Stapleton]])&nbsp;\u2013 3:22\n#\"Turn It Up\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh, Trott)&nbsp;\u2013 3:21\n#\"Not Tonight\" (DeRoberts, David Ryan Harris, Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh)&nbsp;\u2013 3:20\n#\"We Are One\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh)&nbsp;\u2013 2:04\n#\"Everybody but You\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh, Frank Rogers)&nbsp;\u2013 3:30\n#\"Lonely on a Saturday Night\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh, Paslay, Trott)&nbsp;\u2013 3:10\n#\"Why\" (Chris August, Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh, [[James T. Slater]])&nbsp;\u2013 3:19\n#\"Rollin{{'}}\" (Adam Doleac, Hootie and the Blow\ufb01sh, Zach Kale, John King)&nbsp;\u2013 3:17\n#\"Half a Day Ahead\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh)&nbsp;\u2013 3:24\n#\"Change\" (Hootie & the Blow\ufb01sh)&nbsp;\u2013 3:27\n\n==Personnel==\n'''Hootie & the Blowfish'''\n*[[Mark Bryan]]&nbsp;\u2013 guitar; backing vocals; piano on \"Miss California\"; mandolin on \"Hold On\", \"Everybody but You\", and \"Change\"; keyboards on \"Hold On\" and \"Half a Day Ahead\"\n*[[Dean Felber]]&nbsp;\u2013 bass guitar, backing vocals, [[Moog bass]] on \"Turn It Up\" and \"Half a Day Ahead\"\n*[[Darius Rucker]]&nbsp;\u2013 vocals, guitar\n*[[Jim Sonefeld|Jim \"Soni\" Sonefeld]]&nbsp;\u2013 drums, percussion, backing vocals\n\n'''Additional personnel'''\n\n\"New Year's Day\":\n*Sean Badum&nbsp;\u2013 assistant [[Audio recording|recording]] [[audio engineering|engineering]]\n*Michael Brauer&nbsp;\u2013 [[Audio mixing (recorded music)|mixing]]\n*Elliott Elsey&nbsp;\u2013 vocal engineering\n*Ian Fitchuk&nbsp;\u2013 [[Hammond B3]] organ, piano, [[Wurlitzer]] [[electric piano]]\n*Lars Fox&nbsp;\u2013 editing\n*Joe LaPorta&nbsp;\u2013 [[Audio mastering|mastering]] engineering\n*Buckley Miller&nbsp;\u2013 [[Programming (music)|programming]], recording engineering\n*Eric Paslay&nbsp;\u2013 backing vocals\n*[[Jeff Trott]]&nbsp;\u2013 [[Record producer|production]], acoustic and electric guitars, keyboards, backing vocals\n\n\"Miss California\":\n*David Dorn&nbsp;\u2013 keyboards\n*Julian King&nbsp;\u2013 recording eng